lar radius R>12.5km from the work of Oezel and\ncollaborators, the z=0.24 value provides a minimum neutron-star mass of\nM>1.48Msun, instead of M>1.9Msun, when assuming z=0.35.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 12 Sep 2008 10:27:53 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 23 Sep 2008 12:10:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
